@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

   To Install this software you need to copy the file "ASCII-BINARY" to your
C: drawer otherwise this program will be replace by a built-in function 20 times
slower than the extern function.
   If you are a registered user, you need to copy your keyfile into your s: drawer. 
   Some examples are included, they can directly be send to your HP48.
   To transfer your files you need a program such as NComm, TERM ... with
Kermit and/or Xmodem protocols.  

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Info" "What is it?"
@TOC "MAIN"

   This program allows you to manage files from an HP48 or an AMIGA.
Its functions are:
   <1>-Convert an HP file in order to be *DIRECTLY* useable by an AMIGA;
   <2>-Convert an AMIGA file in order to be *DIRECTLY* useable by an HP48;
   <3>-Convert a GROB into an IFF Picture;
   <4>-Convert an IFF picture into a picture useable by HP48:
                       -EXECUTABLE (If the number N of grey density:
                                       is such as 2 < N <= 16);
                       -GROB :HP48's GRaphic OBject
                       -INT :Only the main data are present:
                                Width/Height/Picture Data, ex:"181 64 FF..";
                             To use only in your own programs.
   <5>-Search pictures in an HP file;
   <6>-Convert an HP BINARY file into HP ASCII file;
       (NB:This program works only with HP ASCII files)
   <7>-Convert an HP ASCII file into a HP BINARY file;
       (only, if the HP ASCII file is a disassembled HP Program such as:
       "D9D20........").

*DIRECTLY*?:In fact, these options are not necessary to transfer data but
              are useful to eliminate or to add data which are useful for
              the HP during transfer.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Use" "How to use it?"
@TOC "MAIN"

   Options are on the menu:
Project:
        -New:   Reset Data;
        -Load:
                -File: Load an HP or an AMIGA file ;
                -IFF: Load an IFF picture (! This program isn't AGA);
        -Save:
                -File: Save the file;
                -IFF: Save the last shown picture;
        -Send:   Send a file to HP48
                 (you choose the sending program and the file to save)
        -Quit:   Quit program;

Format:
        -Text:
                -HP48/AMIGA: do action 1
                -AMIGA/HP48: do action 2
                -View file:  ASCII file viewer
        -Picture:
                -HP48/AMIGA: Search all GROBs in an ASCII or BINARY file
                             (converted to ASCII before). These GROBs will be
                             stocked in a menu where they could be
                             individually displayed and eventually saved
                             ( Up and Down Arrow-keys allow you to scroll
                             the screen);
                -AMIGA/HP48: Convert an IFF picture to an HP object.
                             You have to choose the number of grey density
                             and seize a part of the picture (A null box is
                             equivalent to seizing the entire screen)
                             ( Left Alt et Left Amiga keys allow you to have
                             a box which is proportional to the HP screen).
                             Press Enter to valid.;
                -SCANNING:   Scan an HP ASCII file in order to find picture:
                               -Arrow-keys:
                                  -Up/Down:    Screen Scrolling;
                                  -Left/Right: Dec/Inc screen width (step +/- 4);
                               -Numeric Keypad:
                                  -4/6:     Idem (Step +/- 1)
                                  -7/9:     Move the Offset (To centre the picture);
Conversion:
                -Binary to ASCII: Do action 6;
                -ASCII to Binary: Do action 7 (This option is useful to
                 reduce the size of an HP ASCII EXECUTABLE picture).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Remark" "Remark"
@TOC "MAIN"


     -The Buffer size is defined up to 200ko so be careful not to go beyond!!
     -The unregistered version doesn't allow you to save files more than 5Ko. 
      So if you haven't registered, do it it's free !!
     -Be careful this program can't load AGA pictures (with more than 64 colors)
      Because AMOS Pro is not AGA.
      More over, AGA support is not necessary, unless your HP48 is AGA too!!!
     -By pressing LAMIGA A, you can swap the screen with the workbench.
     -This is the first version I distribute, so if you want any ameliorations,
      contact me because I don't know if I have written this program for my own only.
     -Thanks to Yann DEYDIER for having coded an hp program which displays grey levels
      pictures.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TODO" "Todo"
@TOC "MAIN"

      I have written this program one year ago, after the lost of a part of the sources
